examples.en: The town relies on the seasonal tourist industry for jobs.
He relies heavily on his wife for advice.
The director relies on the power of suggestion rather than explicitly showing the murder.
A lowbrow comedy that relies heavily on slapstick for its laughs.
Blind since birth, she relies on her sense of touch to read braille.
The movie relies too much on sinister background music to create the suspense that the plot sorely lacks.
Unlike France, Italy relies on dozens of indigenous regional grape varieties for its prodigious range of wines.
